				<td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=95080&amp;sid=3ed8f16e4074de97004837dfb9e596c4#95080"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Fri Jan 28, 2005 1:59 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
				<td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=95080&amp;sid=3ed8f16e4074de97004837dfb9e596c4"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You have two Vitality pools:  one for adventure experience and one for artisan experience.  Every time you get experience, you use up Vitality from the appropriate pool, and you get a bonus amount added to your experience.  Vitality refreshes at a slow rate whether you are on-line or off-line.  Each character has Vitality pools of their own.  When you switch to an alt and start playing, you use up your alt's Vitality pools but your other character's Vitality pools refresh while you are doing so.
<br />

<br />
In the next upcoming "big patch," they'll be adding windows so you can see how much adventurer and artisan Vitality you have.  They're on Test, but there are issues with them that need to be fixed before they go live.
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
