				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Like the poster above I resigned myself to lvling alts for the other stuff I need.  I don't have the financial resources to buy my stuff so I make it all.  Now I have about 20 gold between all my chars due in large part to a silver cluster I sold for 10g since I didn't have any other use for it.
<br />

<br />
I have a buddy from work that I play with so I convinced him to go for Sage (hehe) and I will go alchemist.  Just for laughs I'm going to go Jeweler with my enchanter.  I lvled up a woodworker to make my quills (and strongboxes for the bank).  While making the strongboxes I discovered I needed an outfitter to make iron sheets so I lvled another character to eventually become a tailor (I want some nice backpacks too).
<br />
This wasn't too much work since I can 2-box and therefore exp and tradeskill 2 chars at once.
<br />

<br />
Since seeing what inks sell for I'm in the process of making a bunch more.  I've already got appIII(a couple appIV's since the patch) spells for all my chars so I'm going to sell a bunch of inks/quills/paper before moving on to the next tier.
<br />

<br />
So I'd say your best bet as a sage is to lvl another char (a woodworker)into his teens which should only take a few days then grind up his tradeskill to 15 or so (or just make an artisan and go right into the crafting).  Use that char to make your quills and paper to cut your costs.  Or since you are a sage already make some tier II iron gual inks to sell and use those funds to help purchase the quills/inks/paper.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=788008" target="_blank" class="postlink">Jeradim</a> - 67 MAG/<a href="http://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/pplayer.vm?characterId=143285101" target="_blank" class="postlink">44 Conjuror/39 Alchy</a>
